<br>
<P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>LARGE SCALE SERVERS: WHAT IS THE PROBLEM?</FONT></B>
<UL>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>network-based storage servers suffer from storage and network
I/O bottleneck</FONT></LI>

<LI>
<B><FONT SIZE=+1>storage I/O bottleneck</FONT></B></LI>

<UL>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>results from the performance gap between the storage and
processor-memory systems</FONT></LI>
</UL>

<LI>
<B><FONT SIZE=+1>network I/O bottleneck</FONT></B></LI>

<UL>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>phenomenon that restricts the throughput at the application
level to a small fraction of the network bandwidth</FONT></LI>

<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>results from lack of integration of OS, network protocols
and architecture</FONT></LI>

<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>several ideas proposed to deal with it</FONT></LI>
</UL>
<FONT SIZE=+1></FONT>&nbsp;
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=+1>finally, most servers are <I>bus-based</I>. But since
bus-based
interconnects do not scale well, large scale systems cannot be built easily.</FONT></LI>
</UL>

